===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*hūsa-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian ''hūs'', Old Saxon ''hūs'' (Dutch [[huis]]), Old High German ''hūs'' (German [[Haus]]), Old Norse [[hús]] (Swedish ''hus''), Gothic -𐌷𐌿𐍃.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /hu:s/

===Noun===
